[http://geonames.usgs.gov/pls/gnispublic/f?p=gnispq:3:::NO::P3_FID:0468585 0468585] |website = |footnotes = }} '''Quincy Township''' is one of twelve [[Township (United States)|townships]] in [[Adams County, Iowa|Adams County]], [[Iowa]], [[United States|USA]]. At the [[2010 United States Census|2010 census]], its population was 1779.<ref name=Census2010>{{cite web|url= http://www.census.gov/2010census/popmap/ipmtext.php?fl=1900393531|title= IA - Quincy township|publisher= [[United States Census Bureau]]|accessdate= March 17, 2013}}</ref> ==Geography== Quincy Township covers an area of {{convert|35.34|sqmi|km2}} and contains one incorporated settlement, [[Corning, Iowa|Corning]] (the county seat). According to the [[United States Geological Survey|USGS]], it contains five cemeteries: Oakland, Old Queen City, Queen City, Quincy and Walnut Grove. ==References== {{Reflist}} ==External links== * [http://www.us-counties.com/localgov/iowa.html US-Counties.com] * [http://www.city-data.com/township/Quincy-Adams-IA.html City-Data.com] {{Adams County, Iowa}} [[Category:Townships in Adams County, Iowa]] {{Iowa-geo-stub}}
